[2] Italy, Rome, fatal case
Date: Wed 28 Jun 2017
Source: Ansa General News [edited]
http://www.ansa.it/english/news/general_news/2017/06/28/unvaccinated-girl-9-died-of-measles-3_851d396c-606e-4858-832b-9112a1eb8464.html


A 9-year-old girl died in a Rome hospital on 28 Apr 2017 from complications from a bout of measles, which she had not been vaccinated against, the Bambino Ges√π Hospital said Wed [28 Jun 2017]. The girl, who lived near Latina south of Rome, was admitted on 19 Apr 2017 with a gene-related disease, a chromosome abnormality.

She came down with a fever and conjunctivitis on 14 Apr 2017 and was diagnosed with measles on 26 Apr 2017. The complications that resulted included pneumonia and respiratory insufficiency, the latter of which was cited as cause of death.

The government recently made it compulsory to have 12 vaccinations before being allowed into school up to the age of 6.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This points out one reason why it is important for children who are immunocompetent without exacerbating conditions to be vaccinated with MMR (measles, mumps, rubella) vaccine, specifically to prevent infection of those most vulnerable who cannot be vaccinated safely.

Maps of Italy can be accessed at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/europe/italy_admin_06.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5145654,75. - Mod.LK]

